<div class="cover">
  <h1>Heather's Guide</h1>
  <div class="subtitle">Impound Manager — Broad &amp; James Towing</div>
  <div class="date">July 2026 • impound-manager.onrender.com</div>
  <div class="tagline">
    This guide covers everything you do in Impound Manager from start to finish — daily intake, BMV searches, sending certified letters, tracking delivery, and handing off to Tina. Follow it top to bottom on your first day.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="toc">
  <h2>What's in this guide</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><a href="#s1">Logging in and your dashboard</a></li>
    <li><a href="#s2">Daily intake — uploading Towbook and BMV files</a></li>
    <li><a href="#s3">Adding a new impound manually</a></li>
    <li><a href="#s4">BMV search queue — working through your list</a></li>
    <li><a href="#s5">A vehicle record — what everything means</a></li>
    <li><a href="#s6">Certified letters — sending and tracking</a></li>
    <li><a href="#s7">Letters dashboard — your four queues</a></li>
    <li><a href="#s8">Scanning envelopes when mail comes back</a></li>
    <li><a href="#s9">Post office run checklist</a></li>
    <li><a href="#s10">File checklist — handing off to Tina</a></li>
    <li><a href="#s11">Invoice Camera</a></li>
  </ol>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 1 -->
<div class="section" id="s1">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">1</div>
    <h2>Logging in and your dashboard</h2>
    <div class="badge">Start here every day</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">How to log in</div>
      <h3>Go to impound-manager.onrender.com</h3>
      <p>Username: <strong>heather</strong> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Password: <strong>BandJ2024!</strong></p>
      <p>After logging in you land on Heather's Dashboard automatically. This is your home base.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Your dashboard</div>
      <h3>The three colored boxes tell you your workload</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782960886871_image.png" alt="Heather's Dashboard">
        <div class="caption">Heather's Dashboard — the three boxes show overdue/urgent, due soon, and on track counts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#fdecea; border-left:4px solid #e53935;">
          <h4 style="color:#c62828;">Red — Overdue / Urgent</h4>
          <ul style="color:#5a1010;">
            <li>Letters past their due date</li>
            <li>These need to go out immediately</li>
            <li>Click to expand and see the list</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#fff8e1; border-left:4px solid #f5a623;">
          <h4 style="color:#8a5a00;">Yellow — Due Soon</h4>
          <ul style="color:#5a3a00;">
            <li>Letters due within the next few days</li>
            <li>Plan your post office run around these</li>
            <li>Click to expand</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout green" style="margin-top:12px;">
        <strong>Green — On Track:</strong> These vehicles have no letter action needed right now. You can ignore them.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Top buttons on your dashboard</div>
      <h3>What the buttons at the top right do</h3>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li><strong>Recalculate</strong> — refreshes the counts. Hit this if the numbers look wrong.</li>
        <li><strong>Envelope Scan</strong> — opens the camera to scan a returned envelope</li>
        <li><strong>Post Office List</strong> — prints today's letter checklist to take to the post office</li>
        <li><strong>+ New Impound</strong> — adds a brand new vehicle manually</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">BMV Search Queue</div>
      <h3>Below the colored boxes is your BMV task list</h3>
      <p>This shows vehicles that need a BMV search done. Work through them one at a time. For each vehicle, do your BMV lookup, then click <strong>BMV Done</strong> if you found owner info, or <strong>No Record</strong> if nothing came up.</p>
      <div class="callout yellow">
        <strong>No Record</strong> flags the vehicle as urgent and notifies Tim. He has to review and decide what to do.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 2 -->
<div class="section" id="s2">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">2</div>
    <h2>Daily intake — uploading Towbook and BMV files</h2>
    <div class="badge">Do this each morning</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Where to go</div>
      <h3>Click "Daily Intake" in the top menu bar</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782960958562_image.png" alt="Daily Intake page">
        <div class="caption">Daily Intake — two drop zones side by side</div>
      </div>
      <p>You'll see two boxes: one for the Towbook CSV export and one for BMV documents.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Left box — Towbook CSV</div>
      <h3>Drop the Towbook export here</h3>
      <div class="workflow-steps">
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">In Towbook, export your impound report as a CSV file</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Drag and drop the file onto the left box, or click "click to browse" to find it</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">The system reads it and adds any new vehicles automatically</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Right box — BMV Documents</div>
      <h3>Drop your LKA and Title Abstract PDFs here</h3>
      <div class="workflow-steps">
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Download your LKA (Last Known Address) and Title Abstract PDFs from the Ohio BMV portal</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">The filenames must contain the word "LKA" or "Abstract" or "Title" — otherwise the system won't recognize them</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Drop them onto the right box. You can drop multiple files at once.</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">The AI reads each PDF and cross-references the owner name and address between the LKA and Title Abstract</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout yellow">
        <strong>If the names or addresses don't match</strong> between the LKA and Title Abstract, the system will flag it for your attention. Check both documents before sending any letter.
      </div>
      <div class="callout blue">
        <strong>BMV portal link:</strong> services.dps.ohio.gov/AbstractAccounts/User/Home
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 3 -->
<div class="section" id="s3">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">3</div>
    <h2>Adding a new impound manually</h2>
    <div class="badge">When needed</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">How to start</div>
      <h3>Click "+ New Impound" in the top right</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961004062_image.png" alt="Add New Impound form top">
        <div class="caption">Add New Impound — top of the form showing impound type and vehicle info</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Impound type</div>
      <h3>Choose PPI or Police</h3>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li><strong>PPI — Private Property Impound</strong>: vehicle towed from private property (apartments, businesses, etc.)</li>
        <li><strong>Police — Law Enforcement</strong>: vehicle brought in by police</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Enter the impound date, storage location (e.g. Row C, Spot 14), and police report number if it's a police impound.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Owner information</div>
      <h3>Fill in the Last Registered Owner section carefully</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961011537_image.png" alt="Owner and Lienholder fields">
        <div class="caption">Owner name and address fields — this is what prints on the certified letter</div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout red">
        <strong>This address is what prints on the certified letter.</strong> Double-check it against your BMV documents before saving.
      </div>
      <p>If there's a lienholder (bank or finance company), fill in that section too. If there's no lienholder, leave it blank — the lienholder letter section won't show up.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Timeline preview</div>
      <h3>The system calculates your letter due dates automatically</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961019673_image.png" alt="Timeline preview at bottom of form">
        <div class="caption">Timeline Preview — shows when Letter 1, Letter 2, and earliest title filing are due</div>
      </div>
      <p>You'll see Letter 1 due date, Letter 2 due date (30 days after Letter 1 is sent), and earliest title filing date (60 days from impound AND 30 days after Letter 2). These calculate automatically based on the impound date you entered.</p>
      <p>Click <strong>+ Add Impound</strong> to save.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 4 -->
<div class="section" id="s4">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">4</div>
    <h2>BMV search queue — working through your list</h2>
    <div class="badge">Daily task</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Your queue</div>
      <h3>The BMV Search Queue shows 100 vehicles at a time</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961362811_image.png" alt="Heather dashboard with BMV queue and BMV Done modal">
        <div class="caption">BMV Search Queue — click BMV Done when you find owner info, No Record if nothing came up</div>
      </div>
      <p>Each row shows the vehicle, VIN, plate, impound date, and how many days it's been in storage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">When you find owner info</div>
      <h3>Click "BMV Done" — enter the owner info you found</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961375531_image.png" alt="BMV Search Complete modal">
        <div class="caption">BMV Search Complete — type the owner name and address you found, then click Mark BMV Complete</div>
      </div>
      <p>Type the owner name and full address in the notes box (e.g. "Owner: John Smith, 123 Main St, Columbus OH 43219"). Click <strong>Mark BMV Complete</strong>. This moves the vehicle into Tina's queue once all letters are done.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">When nothing comes up</div>
      <h3>Click "No Record" — this flags it for Tim</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961382612_image.png" alt="No Record Found modal">
        <div class="caption">No Record Found — this flags the vehicle as urgent and notifies Tim to review</div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout yellow">
        <strong>No Record</strong> means the BMV has no owner or lienholder on file, or the VIN isn't on record, or it's an out-of-state plate with no info. Always add a note explaining what you found (or didn't find).
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 5 -->
<div class="section" id="s5">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">5</div>
    <h2>A vehicle record — what everything means</h2>
    <div class="badge">Reference</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Opening a vehicle</div>
      <h3>Click any vehicle name to open its full record</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961076531_image.png" alt="Vehicle record top — task pipeline and file checklist">
        <div class="caption">Vehicle record — Task Pipeline at top shows where this vehicle is in the process</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Task Pipeline</div>
      <h3>Four tasks — each one unlocks the next</h3>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#f0f0f0;">
          <h4>Task 1 — BMV Search</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; color:#444; margin-top:4px;">Do your BMV lookup. Mark Done or No Record.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#e8f5ee;">
          <h4 style="color:#1a5c38;">Task 2 — 1st Notice Letter</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; color:#1a4a2e; margin-top:4px;">Send Letter 1 certified mail. Confirm delivery when it arrives.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="two-col" style="margin-top:10px;">
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#f0f0f0;">
          <h4>Task 3 — 2nd Notice Letter</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; color:#444; margin-top:4px;">Unlocks 30 days after Letter 1 is sent. Send Letter 2 certified mail.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#f0f0f0;">
          <h4>Task 4 — Ready to File</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; color:#444; margin-top:4px;">Unlocks after all 4 checklist items are confirmed. Hands off to Tina.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Certified Letter Timeline</div>
      <h3>The right side shows letter status and due dates</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961086234_image.png" alt="Vehicle record lower section with letter timeline and actions">
        <div class="caption">Certified Letter Timeline — shows Letter 1 sent date, due date, and Confirm Delivery button</div>
      </div>
      <p>When a letter has been delivered, click <strong>Confirm Delivery</strong> and enter the date. Letter 2 won't show until Letter 1 is marked sent.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Actions panel</div>
      <h3>Buttons at the bottom of every vehicle record</h3>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li><strong>Valuation Report</strong> — shows the vehicle's NADA value and total fees owed</li>
        <li><strong>Collect Payment</strong> — if the owner comes in to pay and retrieve</li>
        <li><strong>Create Invoice</strong> — generates an invoice for the vehicle</li>
        <li><strong>Mark as Released</strong> — removes it from active impounds</li>
        <li><strong>Envelope Scan</strong> — scan a returned envelope for this specific vehicle</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 6 -->
<div class="section" id="s6">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">6</div>
    <h2>Certified letters — sending and tracking</h2>
    <div class="badge">Core daily task</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Sending a letter</div>
      <h3>From the vehicle record, click "Print Letter" to get the letter</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961573821_image.png" alt="Printed certified letter">
        <div class="caption">Printed Letter 1 — Broad &amp; James letterhead, VIA CERTIFIED MAIL, vehicle info auto-filled. Print and mail this.</div>
      </div>
      <p>Print it, put it in the certified mail envelope, take it to the post office. Get a USPS tracking number from the receipt.</p>
      <div class="callout yellow"><strong>Note:</strong> The letter says [REGISTERED OWNER NAME] and [OWNER ADDRESS] until you've entered the owner info in the vehicle record. Make sure the owner info is filled in before printing.</div>
      <div class="callout blue">
        <strong>UPS tracking also works.</strong> Ohio BMV accepts UPS proof of delivery as a substitute for certified mail. The tracking number goes in the same field.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">After you mail it</div>
      <h3>Mark it as Sent and enter the tracking number</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961398251_image.png" alt="Mark Letter as Sent page">
        <div class="caption">Mark Letter as Sent — enter the date sent and the USPS tracking number from your receipt</div>
      </div>
      <div class="workflow-steps">
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Go to the vehicle record</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">In the Certified Letter Timeline, find the letter row</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Click the send/mark button and enter the date sent</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Enter the tracking number from your USPS or UPS receipt</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Click <strong>Mark as Sent</strong></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout green">
        After marking Letter 1 as sent, <strong>Letter 2 is automatically scheduled for 30 days later.</strong> You don't need to do anything else — it will appear in your queue on the right day.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">When delivery is confirmed</div>
      <h3>Confirm delivery after checking UPS/USPS</h3>
      <p>Check the tracking number on UPS.com or USPS.com. Once it shows delivered, go back to the vehicle record and click <strong>Confirm Delivery</strong>.</p>
      <div class="callout yellow">
        <strong>If it shows "Exception"</strong> — that means delivery failed. Check UPS/USPS for the specific reason. Then go to the Letters tab and click <strong>RTS</strong> (Return to Sender) to flag it.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 7 -->
<div class="section" id="s7">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">7</div>
    <h2>Letters dashboard — your four queues</h2>
    <div class="badge">Check daily</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Where to find it</div>
      <h3>Click "Letters" in the top menu bar</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961112603_image.png" alt="Letters and Envelope Scanner dashboard">
        <div class="caption">Letters &amp; Envelope Scanner — four colored stat boxes and five tabs below</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">The four stat boxes</div>
      <h3>At a glance: your full letter status</h3>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#fdecea; border-left:4px solid #e53935;">
          <h4 style="color:#c62828;">Need to Send</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; color:#5a1010; margin-top:4px;">Letters that are overdue or due now. Work through these first.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#fff8e1; border-left:4px solid #f5a623;">
          <h4 style="color:#8a5a00;">Awaiting Delivery</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; color:#5a3a00; margin-top:4px;">Letters sent but not yet confirmed delivered. Check tracking on these.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="two-col" style="margin-top:10px;">
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#fdecea; border-left:4px solid #c62828;">
          <h4 style="color:#c62828;">Returned / RTS</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; color:#5a1010; margin-top:4px;">Letters that came back undeliverable. These need address verification and resending.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#e8f5ee; border-left:4px solid #4caf8a;">
          <h4 style="color:#1a5c38;">Confirmed (30d)</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; color:#1a4a2e; margin-top:4px;">Letters confirmed delivered in the last 30 days. Green means done.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Awaiting Delivery tab</div>
      <h3>Check tracking on each letter in this tab</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961123199_image.png" alt="Awaiting Delivery tab">
        <div class="caption">Awaiting Delivery tab — "Check tracking" badge means this one needs you to look it up on UPS/USPS</div>
      </div>
      <p>For each row with a <span class="pill yellow">Check tracking</span> badge, go to UPS.com or USPS.com and look up that tracking number. Then come back and either click <strong>Confirm Delivered</strong> or <strong>RTS</strong>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Returned / RTS tab</div>
      <h3>Letters that came back — you need to fix the address</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961157341_image.png" alt="Returned RTS tab">
        <div class="caption">Returned/RTS tab — each red row needs address verification. Click "Fix Address" to update and resend.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout red">
        <strong>Action required:</strong> These letters came back. Verify the address in your BMV documents and resend. Click <strong>Fix Address</strong> on each one.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 8 -->
<div class="section" id="s8">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">8</div>
    <h2>Scanning envelopes when mail comes back</h2>
    <div class="badge">When mail returns</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Two ways to scan</div>
      <h3>Use the webcam or upload an image</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961209817_image.png" alt="Scan Envelope modal">
        <div class="caption">Scan Envelope — choose a letter from the dropdown first, then start the camera or upload an image</div>
      </div>
      <div class="workflow-steps">
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Click <strong>Scan Envelope</strong> button (top right of the Letters page, or from a vehicle record)</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Optional: select which letter this envelope is for from the dropdown</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Click <strong>Start Camera</strong> (uses the V4K camera on your desk) or <strong>Upload Image</strong></div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Hold the envelope up to the camera so the address and any stamps/markings are visible</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">The AI reads the envelope and classifies it automatically</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">What happens after scanning</div>
      <h3>The system reads the envelope and updates the letter status</h3>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#e8f5ee;">
          <h4 style="color:#1a5c38;">Delivered</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Logs the delivery date and marks the letter confirmed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#fff8e1;">
          <h4 style="color:#8a5a00;">Address Issue</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Yellow flag — verify the address and resend.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="color-card" style="background:#fdecea; margin-top:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#c62828;">Service Disrupted</h4>
        <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Red flag — immediate resend needed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Bulk upload</div>
      <h3>Scan many envelopes at once with Bulk Envelope Upload</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961449208_image.png" alt="Bulk Envelope Upload page">
        <div class="caption">Bulk Envelope Upload — select 50+ scanned envelope images at once and the AI processes them all</div>
      </div>
      <p>If you have a stack of returned envelopes, scan them all with the document camera, then go to <strong>Heather's Dashboard → Bulk Envelope Upload</strong>. Choose all the image files at once and click <strong>Process Batch</strong>. The AI reads each one and matches it to the right vehicle automatically.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 9 -->
<div class="section" id="s9">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">9</div>
    <h2>Post office run checklist</h2>
    <div class="badge">Print before leaving</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">How to print it</div>
      <h3>Click "Post Office List" → print the page</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961230271_image.png" alt="Post Office Run Checklist">
        <div class="caption">Post Office Run Checklist — prints every overdue and due-today letter with vehicle info, lot location, and a checkbox</div>
      </div>
      <p>The checklist shows every letter that needs to go out, sorted by how overdue they are. Each row has a checkbox so you can check them off as you go.</p>
      <div class="callout blue">
        <strong>Tip:</strong> Also available from the main Overview dashboard via <strong>Print Post Office List</strong> button.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">After the post office run</div>
      <h3>Come back and mark each letter as sent</h3>
      <p>For each letter you mailed, go to that vehicle's record and mark it sent with the tracking number from your receipt. This keeps the system accurate.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 10 -->
<div class="section" id="s10">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">10</div>
    <h2>File checklist — handing off to Tina</h2>
    <div class="badge">Before Tina can file title</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">The four required items</div>
      <h3>All four must be checked before a vehicle moves to Tina</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961076531_image.png" alt="File Checklist on vehicle record">
        <div class="caption">File Checklist — all four boxes must be checked before the vehicle can be handed off to Tina</div>
      </div>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li><strong>LKA document (BMV 2433) uploaded &amp; confirmed</strong> — Last Known Address form from Ohio BMV</li>
        <li><strong>Title search (BMV 1148) uploaded &amp; confirmed</strong> — Title Abstract from Ohio BMV</li>
        <li><strong>UPS delivery confirmation (proof of delivery)</strong> — tracking shows delivered</li>
        <li><strong>Return receipt — physical envelope filed in cabinet</strong> — the green card or signed envelope</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="callout red">
        <strong>All four items are required.</strong> The system will not let the vehicle move to Tina's queue until every box is checked. There are no exceptions.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">What happens next</div>
      <h3>Once all four are checked, the vehicle goes to Tina</h3>
      <p>Tina will see it appear in her "From Heather" queue. She handles the title filing, NADA valuation, and auction routing from there. Your job on this vehicle is done.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 11 -->
<div class="section" id="s11">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">11</div>
    <h2>Invoice Camera</h2>
    <div class="badge">Bonus feature</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">What it does</div>
      <h3>Point a camera at any check or invoice — the AI reads it</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961031025_image.png" alt="Invoice Camera page">
        <div class="caption">Invoice Camera — take a photo or use the V4K webcam to scan a check or invoice</div>
      </div>
      <p>Click <strong>Invoice Cam</strong> in the top menu. Then click <strong>Take Photo</strong> or <strong>Use Webcam</strong>. Hold the document up to the camera. The AI reads the amount, invoice number, and other details and logs the payment automatically.</p>
      <div class="callout green">
        This is useful when an owner comes in to pay — scan their check or cash receipt and it logs immediately without any manual entry.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

