<div class="section" id="s1">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">1</div>
    <h2>Logging in and your dashboard</h2>
    <div class="badge">Start here every day</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">How to log in</div>
      <h3>Go to impound-manager.onrender.com</h3>
      <p>Username: <strong>tina</strong> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Password: <strong>BandJ2024!</strong></p>
      <p>After logging in, click <strong>Tina</strong> in the top menu bar to go to your dashboard.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Your dashboard</div>
      <h3>Four stat boxes across the top</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961311034_image.png" alt="Tina's Dashboard">
        <div class="caption">Tina's Dashboard — four boxes show vehicles from Heather, in progress, ready to file, and needing a decision</div>
      </div>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#fff8e1; border-left:4px solid #f5a623;">
          <h4 style="color:#8a5a00;">From Heather</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">New vehicles Heather just completed and handed off. Check these first.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#e3f0fb; border-left:4px solid #1a7ab5;">
          <h4 style="color:#0d3a5c;">In Progress</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Vehicles you've started working on but haven't filed yet.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="two-col" style="margin-top:10px;">
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#e8f5ee; border-left:4px solid #4caf8a;">
          <h4 style="color:#1a5c38;">Ready to File</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Vehicles that have met the Ohio eligibility requirements. You can file title on these today.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#f0f0f0; border-left:4px solid #888;">
          <h4>Need Decision</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Vehicles where you need to choose sell, junk, or hold before proceeding.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Main list below the boxes</div>
      <h3>The Ready to File list shows all your actionable vehicles</h3>
      <p>Each row shows the vehicle, impound date, when it became eligible (green date = already past, you can file now), NADA value, and buttons to set disposition or file title.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 2 -->
<div class="section" id="s2">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">2</div>
    <h2>Title Eligibility Pipeline — your main work queue</h2>
    <div class="badge">Check daily</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Where to find it</div>
      <h3>Click "Title Eligibility" in the top menu bar</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961267125_image.png" alt="Title Eligibility Pipeline page">
        <div class="caption">Title Eligibility Pipeline — four colored boxes and a list of all vehicles grouped by status</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Four groups</div>
      <h3>Vehicles are sorted into four groups automatically</h3>
      <div class="color-card" style="background:#e8f5ee; border-left:4px solid #4caf8a; margin-bottom:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#1a5c38;">Ready to File</h4>
        <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">All Ohio requirements met. Green "File Title" button on each row. <strong>Start here.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="color-card" style="background:#e3f0fb; border-left:4px solid #1a7ab5; margin-bottom:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#0d3a5c;">Upcoming</h4>
        <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Will be eligible in the next few weeks. Nothing to do yet — just be aware.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="color-card" style="background:#fff8e1; border-left:4px solid #f5a623; margin-bottom:10px;">
        <h4 style="color:#8a5a00;">Blocked on Letters</h4>
        <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Waiting for Heather to finish the letter process. Not your job yet.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="color-card" style="background:#f0f0f0; border-left:4px solid #888;">
        <h4>Recently Filed</h4>
        <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Vehicles you've already filed title on. Done.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 3 -->
<div class="section" id="s3">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">3</div>
    <h2>The Ohio title rule — when you can file and when you can't</h2>
    <div class="badge">Important — read this</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">The basic rule</div>
      <h3>Two requirements must both be met before you can file</h3>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>At least <strong>60 days have passed since the impound date</strong></li>
        <li>At least <strong>30 days have passed since Letter 2 was sent</strong></li>
      </ul>
      <p>Both conditions must be true. The system calculates this automatically and shows the eligible date on each vehicle.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">The NADA value rule — critical</div>
      <h3>Before filing, check whether the vehicle value justifies standard title</h3>
      <div class="rule-box">
        <h4>Ohio Title-by-Abandonment Rule</h4>
        <p><strong>NADA Rough Trade-In Value</strong> minus <strong>total charges owed</strong> (tow + storage) must equal a <strong>negative number</strong>.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px;">Example: NADA value $1,200 — charges owed $3,500 = <strong>-$2,300 ✓ Can file standard title</strong></p>
        <p style="margin-top:4px;">Example: NADA value $8,000 — charges owed $3,500 = <strong>+$4,500 ✗ Cannot file standard title — need court order</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="callout red">
        <strong>If the number is positive</strong> (vehicle is worth more than what's owed), you cannot file title-by-abandonment. A court order is required. Flag this for Tim.
      </div>
      <div class="callout yellow">
        <strong>If NADA shows "—" or $0</strong>, the system couldn't look up a value. You need to check NADA manually or have Tim enter a manual value before you file.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">PO Box rule</div>
      <h3>If the owner's address is a PO Box, special rules apply</h3>
      <p>If the BMV shows the owner's address as a PO Box, the certified letter process has different requirements. The system flags these automatically. If you see a PO Box flag, ask Tim before filing.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 4 -->
<div class="section" id="s4">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">4</div>
    <h2>Filing a title</h2>
    <div class="badge">Core task</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Starting the filing process</div>
      <h3>Click "File Title" on any eligible vehicle</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961286171_image.png" alt="File for Title page">
        <div class="caption">File for Title — shows the vehicle is eligible, with all dates confirmed. Enter the BMV receipt number and notes.</div>
      </div>
      <p>This page confirms the vehicle is eligible, shows the impound date, days in storage, eligible-since date, and when Letter 2 was sent.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Towbook data on every vehicle</div>
      <h3>Scroll down on any vehicle record to see Towbook Data</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961588616_image.png" alt="Towbook Data section">
        <div class="caption">Towbook Data — Stock #, Call #, Invoice #, Account, Balance Due, Have Keys status, and open tasks from Towbook</div>
      </div>
      <p>This section pulls live data from Towbook. The <strong>Have Keys</strong> field is important — if it says No, Robert needs to make keys before the vehicle can go to auction. The Balance Due shows what's currently owed in Towbook.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Damage items on the BMV form</div>
      <h3>Add damage items before generating the BMV 4202</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961650192_image.png" alt="Damage items preset dropdown">
        <div class="caption">Damage Items preset dropdown — select from common presets or type a custom description and dollar amount</div>
      </div>
      <p>The BMV 4202 form allows up to 9 damage items. Use the preset dropdown to quickly add common damage types. The amounts are pre-filled but you can adjust them.</p>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>KEY REPLACEMENT — $350</li>
        <li>FRONT BUMPER — $450</li>
        <li>FENDER — $350</li>
        <li>HOOD — $500</li>
        <li>WINDSHIELD — $300</li>
        <li>WHEEL / TIRE — $300</li>
        <li>QUARTER PANEL — $600</li>
        <li>INTERIOR — $300</li>
        <li>MECHANICAL — $1,200</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="callout yellow"><strong>Max 9 items on the BMV form.</strong> If a vehicle has more damage than that, combine similar items or use the highest-value ones.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Generating the BMV 4202</div>
      <h3>Click "Generate BMV 4202" to create the title packet PDF</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961610515_image.png" alt="Save As dialog for BMV title packet PDF">
        <div class="caption">The BMV 4202 PDF saves automatically with the VIN and date in the filename — save it to your desktop or Downloads</div>
      </div>
      <p>The PDF is auto-filled with all vehicle info, damage items, fees, and your company information. Save it, print it, and take it to the BMV.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">NADA lookup</div>
      <h3>Click "Look Up NADA Value" to get the wholesale value automatically</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961523722_image.png" alt="NADA lookup confirmation dialog">
        <div class="caption">NADA lookup — click OK and the system opens Edmunds and pulls the rough trade-in value automatically (takes 1-2 minutes)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout blue"><strong>Always use the worst-case condition</strong> when looking up NADA — flood damage yes, frame damage yes, fire damage no, title status unknown. This gives the lowest defensible wholesale value, which is what Ohio requires for title-by-abandonment.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">What to fill in</div>
      <h3>Enter the BMV receipt number and any notes</h3>
      <div class="workflow-steps">
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Take the vehicle paperwork to the Ohio BMV</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Submit the title application (BMV form 4202 for PPI, 4205 for police)</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Get the receipt — it has a BMV application number on it</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Come back to the system and enter that number in the <strong>BMV Receipt / Application #</strong> field</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Add any notes (drop-off location, agent name, anything relevant)</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Click the confirm button — this marks the vehicle as <strong>Title Filed</strong> and removes it from the active dashboard</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout yellow">
        <strong>Note:</strong> Once you click confirm, the vehicle moves to the Title Filed tab and disappears from your active queue. Make sure everything is right before clicking.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 5 -->
<div class="section" id="s5">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">5</div>
    <h2>Setting vehicle disposition — sell, junk, or hold</h2>
    <div class="badge">Every vehicle needs a decision</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">What is disposition?</div>
      <h3>After title is filed, every vehicle needs a decision on what happens to it</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961314467_image.png" alt="Disposition modal">
        <div class="caption">Disposition — set SELL, JUNK, or HOLD. The NADA value shows at top to help you decide.</div>
      </div>
      <p>Click <strong>Set</strong> next to any vehicle in your dashboard to open the disposition panel. The NADA value shows at the top so you know what the vehicle is worth.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Three options</div>
      <h3>Choose based on the vehicle's condition and value</h3>
      <div class="three-col">
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#e8f5ee; border-left:4px solid #4caf8a;">
          <h4 style="color:#1a5c38;">SELL</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Auction or private sale. Vehicle goes into the auction pipeline.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#fdecea; border-left:4px solid #e53935;">
          <h4 style="color:#c62828;">JUNK</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Scrap or junk yard. Vehicle gets an invoice for scrap price.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#f0f0f0; border-left:4px solid #888;">
          <h4>HOLD</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Pending decision. Use when you're not sure yet or waiting on Tim.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout blue">
        <strong>Tip from Tim:</strong> If you're not sure, set HOLD and make a note. Tim reviews vehicles on hold regularly.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 6 -->
<div class="section" id="s6">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">6</div>
    <h2>Creating an invoice for a sold or junked vehicle</h2>
    <div class="badge">After disposition is set</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">How to create an invoice</div>
      <h3>Click "Invoice" next to the vehicle or from the vehicle record</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961338064_image.png" alt="Create Invoice page">
        <div class="caption">Create Invoice — choose Sale or Junk/Scrap. For junk, enter the scrap buyer name and price per ton.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">For a sale</div>
      <h3>Select "Sale" tab — enter buyer info and sale price</h3>
      <p>The fee summary on the right shows tow fee plus storage automatically based on what Heather entered when the vehicle was added.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">For junk/scrap</div>
      <h3>Select "Junk / Scrap" tab — enter the junk yard and weight</h3>
      <div class="workflow-steps">
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Enter the <strong>Junk Yard / Scrap Buyer</strong> name</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Enter their address</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Enter the vehicle weight in pounds</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Enter the price per ton they're paying</div></div>
        <div class="workflow-step"><div class="wf-text">Click <strong>Generate Invoice</strong></div></div>
      </div>
      <p>The net proceeds (what B&amp;J keeps after fees) calculates automatically and appears on the right side panel.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 7 -->
<div class="section" id="s7">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">7</div>
    <h2>Vehicle Pipeline Board — tracking through auction stages</h2>
    <div class="badge">Auction workflow</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Where to find it</div>
      <h3>Click "Pipeline" in the top menu bar</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961286171_image.png" alt="Vehicle Pipeline Board">
        <div class="caption">Vehicle Pipeline Board — vehicles move left to right through 8 stages from title pending to sold/junked</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Eight stages</div>
      <h3>Every vehicle that goes to auction moves through these stages</h3>
      <div class="stage-row"><div class="stage-pill" style="background:#e8f5ee; color:#1a5c38;">Title Pending</div> Waiting for BMV to issue title</div>
      <div class="stage-row"><div class="stage-pill" style="background:#4caf8a; color:white;">Title Complete</div> Title in hand — ready for next step</div>
      <div class="stage-row"><div class="stage-pill" style="background:#17a2b8; color:white;">Service Evaluation</div> Jim Welch reviews for service department</div>
      <div class="stage-row"><div class="stage-pill" style="background:#f5a623; color:white;">Auction Candidate</div> Going to auction — needs prep</div>
      <div class="stage-row"><div class="stage-pill" style="background:#e53935; color:white;">Key Inspection</div> Robert makes keys if needed</div>
      <div class="stage-row"><div class="stage-pill" style="background:#9c27b0; color:white;">Live Auction</div> At the auction house</div>
      <div class="stage-row"><div class="stage-pill" style="background:#607d8b; color:white;">Online Auction</div> Listed online</div>
      <div class="stage-row"><div class="stage-pill" style="background:#333; color:white;">Junk Route</div> Going to scrap</div>
      <div class="callout blue" style="margin-top:14px;">
        <strong>Vehicles move through these stages by the drivers and other staff.</strong> Your job is to make sure vehicles enter the pipeline correctly after title is filed and disposition is set to SELL.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 8 -->
<div class="section" id="s8">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">8</div>
    <h2>All Vehicles — active, title filed, released</h2>
    <div class="badge">Reference view</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Where to find it</div>
      <h3>Click "Vehicles" in the top menu bar</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961044093_image.png" alt="All Vehicles — Active tab">
        <div class="caption">All Vehicles — Active tab shows every current impound with days in storage and next action</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Three tabs</div>
      <h3>Active, Title Filed, Released</h3>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#f5f5f5; border:1px solid #ddd;">
          <h4>Active</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">All current impounds. Shows next action needed for each vehicle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="color-card" style="background:#f5f5f5; border:1px solid #ddd;">
          <h4>Title Filed</h4>
          <p style="font-size:13px; margin-top:4px;">Vehicles where title has been filed. Two are shown in your system currently.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="screenshot" style="margin-top:14px;">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961050218_image.png" alt="Title Filed tab">
        <div class="caption">Title Filed tab — vehicles you've already processed</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">Searching</div>
      <h3>Use the search bar at the top to find any vehicle</h3>
      <p>Type a plate number, VIN, owner name, or vehicle year/make/model. Results appear instantly.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 9 -->
<div class="section" id="s9">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="num">9</div>
    <h2>Valuation Report</h2>
    <div class="badge">For every vehicle before filing</div>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">What it shows</div>
      <h3>Click "Valuation Report" from any vehicle record</h3>
      <div class="screenshot">
        <img src="../uploads/1782961180884_image.png" alt="Valuation Report">
        <div class="caption">Valuation Report — shows NADA wholesale value, total fees owed, fee breakdown, and disposition decision checkboxes</div>
      </div>
      <p>The Valuation Report shows:</p>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li><strong>NADA Wholesale Value</strong> — what the vehicle is worth at wholesale (rough trade-in)</li>
        <li><strong>Total Amount Owed</strong> — tow fee + accumulated storage days × daily rate</li>
        <li><strong>Fee Breakdown</strong> — itemized tow fee and storage calculation</li>
        <li><strong>Disposition Decision</strong> — checkboxes for Sell, Junk, or Hold</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-label">The math that matters</div>
      <h3>NADA value minus total owed tells you if you can file standard title</h3>
      <div class="rule-box">
        <h4>Quick check before filing</h4>
        <p>Look at NADA Wholesale Value and Total Amount Owed on this report.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px;"><strong>NADA − Total Owed = negative number → File standard title ✓</strong></p>
        <p style="margin-top:4px;"><strong>NADA − Total Owed = positive number → Need court order, flag Tim ✗</strong></p>
      </div>
      <p>You can also print this report for your records before going to the BMV. Click <strong>Print Report</strong> at the top.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

